sentences: Ralph Jones (February 28, 1921 – June 1, 2000) was an American drummer, best known for his work with Bill Haley & His Comets.

With the recording of the hit "See You Later, Alligator" in December, Jones became the first drummer of the Comets to be featured in a recording session (previous drummers were replaced by session musicians).
He appeared as a member of the band in the 1950s films Rock Around the Clock (1956), Don't Knock the Rock (1957), and Here I Am, Here I Stay (1958).
In 2012, Jones along with most of the other 1950-1960 members of the Comets were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.
